# Voice-AI compatibility page — the /compatibility reference page reached from
# the PromptModal discovery link: the Claude=已验证 marker, the recommended
# opening-prompt block with copy-to-clipboard feedback, and the return-home link.
#
# Restructured for the e2e harness: the scenario carries a per-scenario
# flow-source comment tracing to e2e/flow-inventory.yaml plus a consumption-layer
# tag, and the absolute URL is normalized to a relative path. The final step's
# stale "BOMBSQUAD home page" wording is reconciled to the post-Atlas platform
# homepage.

Feature: Voice AI compatibility reference page
  As a new BombSquad player who is unsure which AI to use
  I want a one-click path from the prompt modal to a list of supported AIs
  And a copy-ready opening prompt to send my AI partner
  So that I can pick a voice AI and brief it without guessing

  Background:
    Given I open /

  # Source: prompt-modal-to-compatibility
  @playwright
  Scenario: Player discovers the compatibility page from the prompt modal and copies the opening prompt
    When I tap "练习"
    Then the prompt modal opens with the practice manual URL
    And I see the link "不确定用哪个 AI？查看支持工具"

    When I click "不确定用哪个 AI？查看支持工具"
    Then the URL path is /compatibility
    And I see a heading "支持的 AI 工具"
    And I see the subtitle "BombSquad 不集成任何 AI 接口，你可以选择任意支持语音对话的 AI 与你协作。"

    And the AI tool list shows the row "Claude" marked "已验证 ✓"
    And the AI tool list shows the row "ChatGPT" marked "未测试 · 邀请反馈"
    And the AI tool list shows the row "Gemini" marked "未测试 · 邀请反馈"
    And no row mentions a required browser or "Clipboard API"

    And I see a heading "告诉 AI 该怎么做"
    And the recommended opening prompt contains "等会儿我会发你一个 URL"
    And the recommended opening prompt contains "每次只回复一步指令"

    When I tap "复制开场白"
    Then the button label changes to "已复制！" within 1 second
    And the system clipboard contains the recommended opening prompt text

    When I click "← 返回 BombSquad 首页"
    Then the URL path is /
    And I am back on the Amiclaw platform homepage
